article.headline: Lipscomb 66, Arkansas Tech 58
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Brandon Brown scored 19 points and had 10 rebounds as Lipscomb outlasted Arkansas Tech 66-58 Monday. Eddie Ard came off the bench to add 13 points for Lipscomb (4-5), and personally outscored the Wonder Boys' reserves by 7 points. Lipscomb outscored the Wonder Boys 19-5 during the first eight minutes of the second half, breaking a 26-26 tie to go up 45-31. Arkansas Tech (5-3) had a balanced scoring attack led by Terrance Whiters with 16 points. Troy Marcus scored 14 and had a team-high eight rebounds, and Jamar Flowers scored 13. Lipscomb had a 10-point advantage at the free throw line, making 21-of-27 to 11-of-15 for the Wonder Boys.
